[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":358},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fnodejs-fullstack-warrior-03-send-email-deploy-heroku\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fnodejs-fullstack-warrior-03-send-email-deploy-heroku\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fnodejs-fullstack-warrior-03-send-email-deploy-heroku\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fnodejs-fullstack-warrior-03-send-email-deploy-heroku\u002F":334,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F07\u002F04\u002Fnodejs-fullstack-warrior-03-send-email-deploy-heroku\u002F":343},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190704\u002F3969699783\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":316,"date":317,"description":318,"extension":319,"lang":320,"meta":321,"navigation":322,"path":323,"readingMinutes":324,"seo":325,"standalone":326,"stem":327,"tags":328,"tldr":331,"updated":317,"url":332,"__hash__":333},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-fullstack-warrior-03-send-email-deploy-heroku.md","Shipping a Mail-Sending App to Heroku (Full-Stack Warrior Node.js, Part 3)","1002304432",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":308},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,37,40,48,54,57,65,72,79,84,90,93,99,110,116,120,127,142,171,174,183,186,192,195,201,204,216,219,225,229,236,242,245,251,257,261,267,273,280,286,294,297,304],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"So we built a little app that sends emails. Now it's time to get it online — let's ship it to Heroku.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"getting-set-up","Getting set up",[17,25,26],{},"Before you can use Heroku, you need to install a couple of things:",[28,29,30,34],"ul",{},[31,32,33],"li",{},"Git",[31,35,36],{},"Heroku CLI",[17,38,39],{},"I won't walk through installing these — here are the links:",[17,41,42],{},[43,44,33],"a",{"href":45,"rel":46},"https:\u002F\u002Fgit-scm.com\u002F",[47],"nofollow",[17,49,50],{},[43,51,36],{"href":52,"rel":53},"https:\u002F\u002Fdevcenter.heroku.com\u002Farticles\u002Fheroku-cli#download-and-install",[47],[12,55,36],{"id":56},"heroku-cli",[17,58,59,60,64],{},"Run ",[61,62,63],"code",{},"heroku -v"," to confirm the install worked.",[17,66,67],{},[68,69],"img",{"alt":70,"src":71},"heroku version check","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fv5Q4yFH.png",[17,73,74,75,78],{},"Next, log in to Heroku. Run ",[61,76,77],{},"heroku login"," and you'll be able to log in through your browser.",[17,80,81],{},[68,82],{"alt":77,"src":83},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F5ptcRoS.png",[17,85,86],{},[68,87],{"alt":88,"src":89},"heroku login in browser","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FtcpWYmg.png",[17,91,92],{},"A successful login looks like this.",[17,94,95],{},[68,96],{"alt":97,"src":98},"login successful","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FqQWzJVg.png",[17,100,101,102,105,106,109],{},"One thing you really need to watch out for before deploying: your ",[61,103,104],{},"package.json",". Do NOT use ",[61,107,108],{},"nodemon"," here — it'll break things.",[17,111,112],{},[68,113],{"alt":114,"src":115},"nodemon in package.json","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FTJLgpLT.png",[12,117,119],{"id":118},"deploying","Deploying",[17,121,122,123,126],{},"First, remember to ",[61,124,125],{},"cd"," into your project directory. Deploying is basically done with Git commands, so run the following:",[17,128,129,130,133,134,137,138,141],{},"(Remember to add a file called ",[61,131,132],{},".gitignore"," with ",[61,135,136],{},"node_modules"," inside it — otherwise you'll commit a bunch of stuff you don't need. If you forget, you can run ",[61,139,140],{},"git reset"," to undo that last commit.)",[143,144,149],"pre",{"className":145,"code":146,"language":147,"meta":148,"style":148},"language-git shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","git init\ngit add .\ngit commit -m 'first'\n","git","",[61,150,151,159,165],{"__ignoreMap":148},[152,153,156],"span",{"class":154,"line":155},"line",1,[152,157,158],{},"git init\n",[152,160,162],{"class":154,"line":161},2,[152,163,164],{},"git add .\n",[152,166,168],{"class":154,"line":167},3,[152,169,170],{},"git commit -m 'first'\n",[17,172,173],{},"Now for the important part — spin up a new Heroku machine:",[143,175,177],{"className":145,"code":176,"language":147,"meta":148,"style":148},"heroku create\n",[61,178,179],{"__ignoreMap":148},[152,180,181],{"class":154,"line":155},[152,182,176],{},[17,184,185],{},"After you run that, you'll see it created a machine for you, named something like peaceful-hot-springs-27518.",[17,187,188],{},[68,189],{"alt":190,"src":191},"creating a Heroku app","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVX7M7Lm.png",[17,193,194],{},"And of course you can see this service in the dashboard too.",[17,196,197],{},[68,198],{"alt":199,"src":200},"the new app in the Heroku dashboard","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F2eHWzbW.png",[17,202,203],{},"The machine's ready, so now we deploy.",[143,205,209],{"className":206,"code":207,"language":208,"meta":148,"style":148},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","git push heroku master\n","js",[61,210,211],{"__ignoreMap":148},[152,212,213],{"class":154,"line":155},[152,214,207],{"class":215},"sMAXC",[17,217,218],{},"During the push, Heroku installs everything it needs for you. Once it's done, you can click on the machine.",[17,220,221],{},[68,222],{"alt":223,"src":224},"clicking the app","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FdtakKJW.png",[12,226,228],{"id":227},"environment-variables","Environment variables",[17,230,231,232,235],{},"Before you can actually use the app, you need to add environment variables to Heroku — otherwise it can't send emails. Go into the machine and click ",[61,233,234],{},"Settings",".",[17,237,238],{},[68,239],{"alt":240,"src":241},"Heroku settings","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F4Wl813r.png",[17,243,244],{},"Then add your environment variables below.",[17,246,247],{},[68,248],{"alt":249,"src":250},"adding environment variables","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FjwN3SA7.png",[17,252,253],{},[68,254],{"alt":255,"src":256},"environment variables added","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FmgX7ied.png",[12,258,260],{"id":259},"opening-the-app","Opening the app",[17,262,263,264,235],{},"The way I usually open the app is straight from the machine — top-right corner, ",[61,265,266],{},"Open App",[17,268,269],{},[68,270],{"alt":271,"src":272},"open the app","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FhVvZs6v.png",[17,274,275,276,279],{},"Then add ",[61,277,278],{},"\u002Fusers\u002Fmailsend"," to the end of the URL, and you'll land on the send page.",[17,281,282],{},[68,283],{"alt":284,"src":285},"the send page","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FzjvVdu1.png",[17,287,288,289,293],{},"From here you can try sending. You might hit an error during this step — it's the same \"blocked\" situation as before, so just follow ",[43,290,292],{"href":291},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190704\u002F184223391\u002F","this post"," (article in Mandarin) to deal with it.",[17,295,296],{},"That's basically it, no real trouble from here. I'll drop the live send URL below — feel free to play with it if you're bored.",[17,298,299],{},[43,300,303],{"href":301,"rel":302},"https:\u002F\u002Fpeaceful-hot-springs-27518.herokuapp.com\u002Fusers\u002Fmailsend",[47],"Tiny app, could be taken down anytime",[305,306,307],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}",{"title":148,"searchDepth":161,"depth":161,"links":309},[310,